     = \n| toll                = \n| map_type            = New South Wales\n| map_relief          = 1\n| map_dot_label       = \n| map_image           = \n| map_size            = \n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = Location of Mulwala Bridge on the [[New South Wales]] and [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] border\n| extra               = <!-- extra = module = embed = -->\n}}\nThe '''Mulwala Bridge''' is a [[road bridge]] over [[Lake Mulwala]], formed by a [[weir]] on the [[Murray River]], on the state border between [[New South Wales]] and [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] in Australia. The bridge links the border towns of [[Yarrawonga]] in Victoria and [[Mulwala]] in New South Wales. The bridge was built in 1924 and designed by [[Percy Allan]] using a [[Pratt truss]].<ref name=\"RTA\">{{cite web|title=Mulwala Bridge over Murray River|url=http://www.rta.nsw.gov.au/cgi-bin/index.cgi?action=heritage.show&id=4301017|publisher=Roads and Transport Authority (NSW)|accessdate=19 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{stack|{{Portal|New South Wales|Transport|Engineering|Australian roads}}}}\n* [[List of crossings of the Murray River]]\n* [[List of bridges in Australia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n{{River item box\n|River = [[Murray River]]\n|upstream = Yarrawonga railway bridge\n|upsub = \n|downstream = Gonn Crossing Bridge\n|downsub = \n|table = \n|location = }}\n\n{{Road infrastructure in regional New South Wales}}\n\n[[Category:Crossings of the Murray River]]\n[[Category:Road bridges in New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Bridges completed in 1924]]\n[[Category:1924 establishments in Australia]]\n[[Category:Truss bridges in Australia]]\n[[Category:Bridges designed by Percy Allan]]\n[[Category:Allan truss bridges]]\n[[Category:Borders of New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Borders of Victoria (Australia)]]\n\n\n{{Australia-bridge-struct-stub}}\n{{NewSouthWales-struct-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox bridge\n| name                = Mulwala Bridge\n| native_name         = \n| native_name_lang    = \n| image               = MulwalaBridge.JPG\n| image_upright       = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = \n| coordinates         = {{coord|-36.0043|146.0041|type:landmark_region:AU|display=title,inline|format=dms}}<!-- {{Coord}} -->\n| os_grid_reference   = \n| carries             = \n| crosses             = [[Lake Mulwala]], [[Murray River]]\n| locale              = \n| official_name       = \n| other_name          = \n| named_for           = [[Mulwala]]\n| owner               = \n| maint               = \n| heritage            = \n| id                  = \n| id_type             = \n| website             = \n| preceded            = John Foord Bridge\n| followed            = Yarrawonga Rail Bridge\n| design              = [[Pratt truss]]\n| material            = \n| material1           = \n| material2           = \n| length              = \n| width               = \n| height              = \n| depth               = \n| traversable         = \n| towpath             = \n| mainspan            = \n| number_spans        = \n| piers_in_water      = \n| load                = \n| clearance_above     = \n| clearance_below     = \n| lanes               = \n| life                = \n| num_track           = \n| track_gauge         = \n| structure_gauge     = \n| electrification     = \n| architect           = \n| designer            = [[Percy Allan]]\n| contracted_designer = \n| winner              = \n| engineering         = \n| builder             = \n| fabricator          = \n| begin               = \n| complete            = 1924\n| cost                = \n| open                = <!-- or | opening = -->\n| inaugurated         = \n| rebuilt             = \n| collapsed           = \n| closed              = \n| replaces            = \n| replaced_by         = \n| traffic             = \n| toll                = \n| map_type            = New South Wales\n| map_relief          = 1\n| map_dot_label       = \n| map_image           = \n| map_size            = \n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = Location of Mulwala Bridge on the [[New South Wales]] and [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] border\n| extra               = <!-- extra = module = embed = -->\n}}\nThe '''Mulwala Bridge''' is a [[road bridge]] over [[Lake Mulwala]], formed by a [[weir]] on the [[Murray River]], on the state border between [[New South Wales]] and [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] in Australia. The bridge links the border towns of [[Yarrawonga]] in Victoria and [[Mulwala]] in New South Wales. The bridge was built in 1924 and designed by [[Percy Allan]] using a [[Pratt truss]].<ref name=\"RTA\">{{cite web|title=Mulwala Bridge over Murray River|url=http://www.rta.nsw.gov.au/cgi-bin/index.cgi?action=heritage.show&id=4301017|publisher=Roads and Transport Authority (NSW)|accessdate=19 July 2010}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n{{River item box\n|River = [[Murray River]]\n|upstream = Yarrawonga railway bridge\n|upsub = \n|downstream = Gonn Crossing Bridge\n|downsub = \n|table = \n|location = }}\n\n{{Road infrastructure in regional New South Wales}}\n\n[[Category:Crossings of the Murray River]]\n[[Category:Road bridges in New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Bridges completed in 1924]]\n[[Category:1924 establishments in Australia]]\n[[Category:Truss bridges in Australia]]\n[[Category:Bridges designed by Percy Allan]]\n[[Category:Allan truss bridges]]\n[[Category:Borders of New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Borders of Victoria (Australia)]]\n\n\n{{Australia-bridge-struct-stub}}\n{{NewSouthWales-struct-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rangasyd", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:+see also", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mulwala_Bridge"}
{"title_page": "2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Final", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Infobox football match\n| title              = 2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Final\n| image              = Est\u00e1dio Maracan\u00e3 1.jpg\n| caption            = The [[Maracan\u00e3 Stadium|Est\u00e1dio do Maracan\u00e3]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]] hosted the final.\n| event              = [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica]]\n| team1              = [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]]\n| team1association   = {{flagicon|BRA|size=30px}}\n| team1score         = 3\n| team2              = [[Peru national football team|Peru]]\n| team2association   = {{flagicon|PER|football|size=30px}}\n| team2score         = 1\n| date               = {{Start date|2019|7|7|df=y}}\n| stadium            = [[Maracan\u00e3 Stadium|Est\u00e1dio do Maracan\u00e3]]\n| city               = [[Rio de Janeiro]]\n| man_of_the_match1a = [[Everton Soares|Everton]] (Brazil)<ref name=\"MOTM\" />\n| referee            = [[Roberto Tobar]] ([[Football Federation of Chile|Chile]])\n| attendance         = 69,968\n| weather            =\n| previous           = [[Copa Am\u00e9rica Centenario Final|2016]]\n| next               = ''2021''\n}}\nThe '''2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Final''' was a [[Association football|football]] match that took place on 7 July 2019 at the [[Maracan\u00e3 Stadium|Est\u00e1dio do Maracan\u00e3]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]], Brazil to determine the winner of the [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica]].\n\nThe match featured [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], the tournament hosts, and [[Peru national football team|Peru]], in which Brazil won the final 3\u20131 for their ninth [[Copa Am\u00e9rica]] title, and their first since [[2007 Copa Am\u00e9rica|2007]].<ref name=\"2007-1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jul/07/copa-america-brazil-peru-final-gabriel-jesus |title=Brazil end Copa Am\u00e9rica drought with victory over Peru in final|date=7 July 2019|website=theguardian.com|publisher=Guardian News & Media Limited|access-date=8 July 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"2007-2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/es-cl/news/4778/main/2016/06/23/23609392/historia-de-la-copa-am%C3%A9rica-2007-robinho-fue-messi|title=En 2007, Brasil le gan\u00f3 a Argentina la Copa Am\u00e9rica. {{!}} Goal.com|website=www.goal.com|year=2007|language=es}}</ref><ref name=\"2007-3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.alairelibre.cl/noticias/deportes/copa-america/venezuela-2007/brasil-destrozo-el-favoritismo-argentino-y-se-corono-bicampeon-de/2007-07-15/190805.html|title=Brasil destroz\u00f3 el favoritismo argentino y se coron\u00f3 bicampe\u00f3n de Am\u00e9rica|last=Comunicaciones|first=Compa\u00f1ia Chilena de|website=alairelibre.cl|language=Spanish|date=July 15, 2007|access-date=July 15, 2007}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nThis edition was the fifth hosted by the Brazil. This match marks the third time Peru reached the final of which two times have been winners. Their last championship (including worldwide tournaments) was won in [[1975 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1975]].<ref name=\"calendar\">{{cite web |url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/conmebol-y-comite-organizador-local-definen-calendario-de-la-conmebol-copa-america-brasil-2019 |title=CONMEBOL y Comit\u00e9 Organizador Local definen calendario de la CONMEBOL Copa Am\u00e9rica Brasil 2019 |trans-title=CONMEBOL and Local Organizing Committee define the calendar of the CONMEBOL Copa Am\u00e9rica Brazil 2019 |publisher=CONMEBOL.com |date=18 December 2018 |access-date=18 December 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url= https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jul/02/argentina-brazil-copa-america-match-report|title =Firmino and Jesus strike as Brazil sink Argentina in Copa Am\u00e9rica semi-final|date=2 July 2019|work=Guardian|accessdate=3 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{citeweb|url= https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/jul/04/peru-set-up-brazil-clash-in-copa-america-final-after-resounding-win-over-chile|title =Peru set up Brazil clash in Copa Am\u00e9rica final after resounding win over Chile|date=4 July 2019|work=Guardian|accessdate=4 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://peru.com/retro/peru/peru-campeon-copa-america-1975-fotos-noticia-436255|title=Per\u00fa, campe\u00f3n de la Copa Am\u00e9rica 1975|last=Peru.com|date=February 3, 2016|website=Per\u00fa.com|language=es|access-date=February 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elcomercio.pe/deporte-total/seleccion/copa-america-1975-gol-sotil-le-dio-titulo-peru-236281|title=Copa Am\u00e9rica 1975: el gol de Sotil que le dio t\u00edtulo a Per\u00fa|last=Elcomercio.pe|first=Redacci\u00f3n|date=October 10, 2015|website=El Comercio|language=es|access-date=October 10, 2015}}</ref> Meanwhile, it is Brazil's nineteenth final, of which eight times have been winners. The last final that Brazil won was in the [[2007 Copa America|2007]] hosted in Venezuela, after defeating Argentina by 3 goals to 0.<ref name=\"2007-1\" /><ref name=\"2007-2\" /><ref name=\"2007-3\" />\n\n==Route to the final==\n{{Further|2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n\n{| style=\"width:100%; text-align:center;\"\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#99CCFF;\"\n! colspan=\"2\" | Brazil\n! Round\n! colspan=\"2\" | Peru\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#C1E0FF;\"\n| Opponents\n| Result\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica#Group stage|Group stage]]\n| Opponents\n| Result\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|BOL}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A#Brazil vs Bolivia|3\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF;\" | Match 1\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|VEN}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A#Venezuela vs Peru|0\u20130]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|VEN}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A#Brazil vs Venezuela|0\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF;\" | Match 2\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|BOL}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A#Bolivia vs Peru|3\u20131]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|PER}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A#Peru vs Brazil|5\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF;\" | Match 3\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|BRA}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A#Peru vs Brazil|0\u20135]]\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''[[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A|Group A]] winners'''\n<center>{{2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica group tables|Group A|only_pld_pts=yes|showteam=BRA}}</center>\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF;\" | Final standings\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''[[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group A|Group A]] third place'''\n<center>{{2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica group tables|Group A|only_pld_pts=yes|showteam=PER}}</center>\n|- style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#C1E0FF;\"\n| Opponents\n| Result\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica knockout stage|Knockout stage]]\n| Opponents\n| Result\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|PAR}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica knockout stage#Brazil vs Paraguay|0\u20130]] {{pso|4\u20133}}\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF;\" | Quarter-finals\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|URU}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica knockout stage#Uruguay vs Peru|0\u20130]] {{pso|5\u20134}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|ARG}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica knockout stage#Brazil vs Argentina|2\u20130]]\n| style=\"background:#C1E0FF;\" | Semi-finals\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | {{fb|CHI}}\n| [[2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica knockout stage#Chile vs Peru|3\u20130]]\n|}\n\n==Match==\n===Summary===\n[[Everton Soares|Everton]] opened the scoring for Brazil after 15 minutes with a low right footed volley from eight yards out after a [[Gabriel Jesus]] cross from the right. Peru were awarded a penalty after 44 minutes when the ball struck the hand of  [[Thiago Silva]], with [[Paolo Guerrero]] scoring with a low shot to the right corner of the net. Brazil went back in front a minute later with a shot to the left corner of the net from inside the penalty area from Gabriel Jesus.<ref>{{citeweb|url= https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2019/jul/06/copa-america-final-brazil-peru-live|title = Brazil 3 Peru 1: as it happened|date=7 July 2019|work=Guardian|accessdate=16 August 2019}}</ref>\t\nGabriel Jesus was shown a red card after 70 minutes after picking up a second yellow for jumping into the back of [[Carlos Zambrano (footballer)|Carlos Zambrano]]. Substitute [[Richarlison]] made it 3\u20131 in the 90th minute with a penalty, shooting low to the left corner after Everton was fouled by Carlos Zambrano.<ref>{{citeweb|url= https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48897389|title = Brazil 3 Peru 1|date=7 July 2019|work=BBC Sport|accessdate=16 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Details===\n<section begin=Final />{{Football box\n|date       = {{Start date|2019|7|7|df=y}}\n|time       = 17:00\n|team1      = {{fb-rt|BRA}}\n|score      = {{score link|2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica knockout stage#Final|3\u20131|2019 Copa Am\u00e9rica Final}}\n|team2      = {{fb|PER}}\n|goals1     =\n*[[Everton Soares|Everton]] {{goal|15}}\n*[[Gabriel Jesus]] {{goal|45+3}}\n*[[Richarlison]] {{goal|90|pen.}}\n|goals2     =\n*[[Paolo Guerrero|Guerrero]] {{goal|44|pen.}}\n|stadium    = [[Maracan\u00e3 Stadium|Est\u00e1dio do Maracan\u00e3]], [[Rio de Janeiro]]\n|attendance = 69,968\n|referee    = [[Roberto Tobar]] ([[Football Federation of Chile|Chile]])\n|report     = http://estadisticas.conmebol.com/html/v3/index.html?channel=deportes.futbol.copaamerica.462536&lang=es_LA\n}}<section end=Final />\n<section begin=Lineups />\n{| width=92%\n|-\n|{{Football kit\n |pattern_la = _bra19H\n |pattern_b  = _bra19H\n |pattern_ra = _bra19H\n |pattern_sh = _bra18h\n |pattern_so = _bra18A\n |leftarm    = FFCC00\n |body       = FFCC00\n |rightarm   = FFCC00\n |shorts     = 0000FF\n |socks      = 003CFF\n |title      = Brazil\n}}\n|{{Football kit\n |pattern_la = _per19h\n |pattern_b  = _per19h\n |pattern_ra = _per19h\n |pattern_sh = _per19h\n |pattern_so =\n |leftarm    = FFFFFF\n |body       = FFFFFF\n |rightarm   = FFFFFF\n |shorts     = FFFFFF\n |socks      = FFFFFF\n |title      = Peru\n}}\n|}\n\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|valign=\"top\